<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/195: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-02">June 2, 1942</date>.<lb/>[Received June
                                    2—12:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2424. Exchange negotiations—Japan. Department’s 1392 [<hi rend="italic">1329</hi>], May 23. Swiss Legation Tokio
                                telegraphed May 31 following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Japanese Government sees no objection to separate British
                                        and American exchanges so that American exchange can take
                                        place about July 10 as agreed.”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>